                                                                                                               Primary school bans school
                            
	London, Jan. 3: A new primary school has banned the use of the word school in its title because it has negative connotations.         
	Watercliffe Meadow primary in Sheffield is to be known as a place for learning after governors decided that the traditional description sounded too institutional. The 6 million learning experience, which opens on Monday, has got rid of the traditional school bell at the end of lessons.                            THE DAILY TELEGRAPH                                                                                                                                                                     
